I'm not calming shit.

258
00:10:27,192 --> 00:10:28,891
You brought this kid into my life.

259
00:10:28,927 --> 00:10:30,827
You put my daughter's
future in jeopardy.

260
00:10:30,862 --> 00:10:32,261
- Look, I know you're upset...
- Upset?

261
00:10:32,296 --> 00:10:35,631
You're lucky I don't
lay you out right now.

262
00:10:36,169 --> 00:10:38,136
Robert, listen to me.

263
00:10:38,171 --> 00:10:40,138
Mike Ross is a good man.

264
00:10:40,173 --> 00:10:41,607
He came to me from nothing.

265
00:10:41,642 --> 00:10:42,941
I saw something in him,

266
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:44,576
and you did, too, and
that's why you're here.

267
00:10:44,612 --> 00:10:46,177
No, I was here to get
him to turn on you,

268
00:10:46,213 --> 00:10:47,679
but he's too stupid to do that.

269
00:10:48,020 --> 00:10:50,153
And I don't know if he's gonna
change his mind or not,

270
00:10:50,188 --> 00:10:51,487
but I don't care anymore,

271
00:10:51,523 --> 00:10:56,092
and I don't give a damn if I
ever see either of you again.

272
00:10:56,127 --> 00:10:57,427
Did you hear that?

273
00:10:57,462 --> 00:10:59,729
He's not Mike Ross's
attorney anymore... I am.

274
00:10:59,765 --> 00:11:01,798
So let me the hell in.

275
00:11:05,236 --> 00:11:07,303
Robert Zane? Really?

276
00:11:07,338 --> 00:11:08,504
I'm hurt.

277
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:10,040
- Harvey, this is real.
- I know.

278
00:11:10,075 --> 00:11:11,942
And the first we need to figure
out is who tipped them off.

279
00:11:11,977 --> 00:11:13,309
Why the hell do we need to do that?

280
00:11:13,344 --> 00:11:14,578
Because if we're gonna
get you out of this,

281
00:11:14,613 --> 00:11:16,179
we have to know every damn
thing they have on you.

282
00:11:16,214 --> 00:11:17,647
Are you crazy? There's
no getting out of this.

283
00:11:17,683 --> 00:11:19,849
I haven't lost a case before,
and I'm not about to start now.

284
00:11:19,885 --> 00:11:21,184
This isn't just some other case.

285
00:11:21,219 --> 00:11:22,719
They're gonna check the
facts, and when they do...

286
00:11:22,754 --> 00:11:24,253
They're gonna find
what we let them find.

287
00:11:24,289 --> 00:11:26,695
- You can't know that.
- Yes, I can.

288
00:11:26,696 --> 00:11:28,696
- That's bullshit!
- This is not bullshit!

289
00:11:28,732 --> 00:11:29,964
Look, we can win this case.

290
00:11:29,999 --> 00:11:31,699
I don't care about winning this thing.

291
00:11:31,735 --> 00:11:32,667
What the hell is wrong with you?

292
00:11:32,702 --> 00:11:34,402
Harvey, I did this!

293
00:11:44,894 --> 00:11:49,030
You didn't do shit because
they don't have shit.

294
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:53,767
What the hell are you talking about?

295
00:11:53,803 --> 00:11:56,304
Mike, you're in the Harvard database.

296
00:11:56,339 --> 00:11:58,172
You have a transcript.

297
00:11:58,207 --> 00:11:59,340
You're in the bar.

298
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:01,309
You're a practicing attorney.

299
00:12:01,344 --> 00:12:02,810
Those facts are real,

300
00:12:02,845 --> 00:12:04,412
just like every case you ever worked on

301
00:12:04,447 --> 00:12:06,347
and every person you've
helped along the way.

302
00:12:09,076 --> 00:12:10,541
Harvey, this woman's not joking.

303
00:12:10,577 --> 00:12:12,844
That woman has to show you're a fraud,

304
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:14,813
but as far as the world knows,
you're a goddamn lawyer,

305
00:12:14,848 --> 00:12:16,447
and that's the way it's gonna stay.

306
00:12:16,483 --> 00:12:17,949
And don't forget...

307
00:12:17,985 --> 00:12:19,450
we don't need to prove you're a lawyer.

308
00:12:19,486 --> 00:12:21,820
She needs to prove you're not.

309
00:12:23,857 --> 00:12:25,190
Rachel, calm down.

310
00:12:25,225 --> 00:12:26,457
I can't calm down.

311
00:12:26,493 --> 00:12:28,559
No one will tell me anything.
I can't go and see him.

312
00:12:28,595 --> 00:12:29,995
It is the worst moment of his life,

313
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:31,640
and I'm not there for him.

314
00:12:31,641 --> 00:12:32,706
Well, you will be when you can.

315
00:12:32,742 --> 00:12:34,074
On top of all that,

316
00:12:34,109 --> 00:12:36,843
I don't know what my dad's
gonna do when he gets there.

317
00:12:36,879 --> 00:12:39,146
You called your dad?

318
00:12:39,181 --> 00:12:41,382
Rachel, I don't think
that was a good idea.

319
00:12:41,417 --> 00:12:42,883
Well, I couldn't just sit
here and do nothing.

320
00:12:42,918 --> 00:12:44,117
Mike's been arrested.

321
00:12:44,153 --> 00:12:46,987
Jessica's talking about
unindicted co-conspirators.

322
00:12:47,022 --> 00:12:48,789
Okay, well then, he and Harvey
will just have to work it out.

323
00:12:48,824 --> 00:12:50,391
And what if they don't?

324
00:12:51,022 --> 00:12:52,889
Rachel, when I was in trouble,

325
00:12:52,924 --> 00:12:54,590
Harvey got me out of it.

326
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:56,225
This is what he does.

327
00:12:56,261 --> 00:13:00,129
I am telling you, he will
get Mike out of this.

328
00:13:00,164 --> 00:13:01,563
It's just...

329
00:13:02,733 --> 00:13:05,467
The thought of him...

330
00:13:05,503 --> 00:13:07,970
in there all alone.

331
00:13:08,006 --> 00:13:10,373
He'll be okay.

332
00:13:10,408 --> 00:13:13,575
It's just one night.

333
00:13:21,979 --> 00:13:23,511
Man, what are you looking at?

334
00:13:23,546 --> 00:13:24,579
Nothing.

335
00:13:24,614 --> 00:13:26,348
Your eyes are going up
and down on me, man.

336
00:13:26,383 --> 00:13:28,783
It don't feel like nothing.

337
00:13:28,818 --> 00:13:31,786
They all say, "Nothing.
Wasn't doing nothing."

338
00:13:32,607 --> 00:13:35,056
It don't matter what you say
and do once you're inside.

339
00:13:35,092 --> 00:13:37,459
Little snot like you won't last a week.

340
00:13:39,687 --> 00:13:41,420
You hear what I said?

341
00:13:41,456 --> 00:13:42,888
You won't last a week in there.

342
00:13:42,924 --> 00:13:44,490
You might not last a night in here.

343
00:13:44,525 --> 00:13:45,858
Listen, man...

344
00:13:47,628 --> 00:13:49,695
Hey! Get your hands off
him, you piece of shit.

345
00:13:51,165 --> 00:13:52,364
You're lucky, but they
won't be here all night.

346
00:13:52,399 --> 00:13:53,599
Yeah, neither will you.

347
00:13:53,634 --> 00:13:54,767
Hey, it's fine. It's fine. It's fine.

348
00:13:54,802 --> 00:13:56,836
Leave him in here with me. It's cool.

349
00:13:56,871 --> 00:13:59,037
I mean, unless you're gonna
let a federal marshal

350
00:13:59,073 --> 00:14:00,873
beat the shit out of me
just to try and scare me

351
00:14:00,908 --> 00:14:02,140
into making a deal.

352
00:14:06,413 --> 00:14:08,347
Agent Ron Da'Mico, right?

353
00:14:11,577 --> 00:14:14,145
Yeah, I saw your picture out in the hall

354
00:14:14,180 --> 00:14:16,380
getting a commendation from the U.S.
Attorney.

355
00:14:16,416 --> 00:14:19,083
Of course, you didn't have
a beard in that photo,

356
00:14:19,118 --> 00:14:20,717
but you look the same to me.

357
00:14:20,753 --> 00:14:23,020
You're a smart kid.

358
00:14:23,056 --> 00:14:25,289
I guess that's how you got away
with what you got away with.

359
00:14:25,324 --> 00:14:29,927
But you didn't really get
away with it, did you?

360
00:14:30,548 --> 00:14:33,282
I am a marshal, but the
next guy won't be,

361
00:14:33,317 --> 00:14:35,184
and you give him that
know-it-all attitude,

362
00:14:35,219 --> 00:14:37,687
and like I said, you won't last a night.

363
00:14:40,224 --> 00:14:42,659
Yeah, well, for the record,
I'm not getting sent away,

364
00:14:42,694 --> 00:14:45,427
but even if I was, it wouldn't
be a place like that.

365
00:14:45,463 --> 00:14:47,864
Oh, if you think you're
going to Club Fed...

366
00:14:47,899 --> 00:14:50,599
You don't know Anita Gibbs.

367
00:14:50,635 --> 00:14:52,334
Sleep well, sweetheart.

368
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:10,466
How is he?

369
00:15:10,501 --> 00:15:12,101
He's in custody.

370
00:15:12,594 --> 00:15:15,228
And the bail hearing?

371
00:15:15,263 --> 00:15:16,696
I don't know,

372
00:15:16,731 --> 00:15:18,163
because I'm not representing him.

373
00:15:18,199 --> 00:15:19,865
Now, are you done asking me questions?

374
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:21,200
Because I have a few of my own,

375
00:15:21,236 --> 00:15:24,270
like how the hell could you do this?

376
00:15:24,305 --> 00:15:26,372
Dad, because I love him.

377
00:15:26,407 --> 00:15:28,407
That's sweet, but you
sound like a teenager,

378
00:15:28,443 --> 00:15:30,742
and right now your mother is sobbing,

379
00:15:30,743 --> 00:15:32,143
knowing what you've done to yourself.

380
00:15:32,178 --> 00:15:35,379
Dad, Mike is the same man
that you worked with.

381
00:15:35,414 --> 00:15:37,081
And you said yourself there are things

382
00:15:37,116 --> 00:15:39,316
that you did in your past
that you're not proud of.

383
00:15:39,351 --> 00:15:41,252
Don't you dare compare me to him.

384
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:43,410
I am not a fraud.

385
00:15:43,445 --> 00:15:45,044
I am not a criminal.

386
00:15:51,353 --> 00:15:53,653
Rachel...

387
00:15:53,689 --> 00:15:57,190
Rachel...

388
00:15:57,465 --> 00:15:59,832
I tried to get him out,

389
00:15:59,868 --> 00:16:01,467
but he's living in a dream world,

390
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:03,302
and so are you if you
think this boy is done

391
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:04,336
ruining your life.

392
00:16:04,372 --> 00:16:05,572
Why did you even come here?

393
00:16:05,607 --> 00:16:08,697
I came here to tell you
to look in the mirror

394
00:16:08,698 --> 00:16:11,166
and get rid of him.

395
00:16:13,670 --> 00:16:17,105
I can't do that.

396
00:16:25,859 --> 00:16:28,559
Then I can't help you.

397
00:16:46,815 --> 00:16:48,615
I was wondering when you
were gonna pay me a visit.

398
00:16:48,651 --> 00:16:49,650
You know who I am?

399
00:16:49,685 --> 00:16:50,984
I know everyone in my crosshairs.

400
00:16:51,019 --> 00:16:53,353
Now pass me the cream and
tell me what you want.

401
00:16:53,389 --> 00:16:55,522
I want to know why you
arrested my associate

402
00:16:55,557 --> 00:16:57,090
without just cause.

403
00:16:57,125 --> 00:16:58,692
Because Mike Ross is a fraud,

404
00:16:58,727 --> 00:17:00,327
and I'm gonna make sure he never sees

405
00:17:00,362 --> 00:17:01,895
the inside of a courtroom again,

406
00:17:01,930 --> 00:17:03,830
unless he's wearing an orange jumpsuit.

407
00:17:04,794 --> 00:17:06,184
If you'll excuse me,

408
00:17:06,185 --> 00:17:08,018
I have an arraignment to prepare for.

409
00:17:08,053 --> 00:17:10,854
What if I was to tell you off the record

410
00:17:10,889 --> 00:17:12,622
Mike Ross was about to resign?

411
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:14,457
I'd say that sounds very convenient.

412
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:16,159
Well, it isn't. I'm
telling you the truth.

413
00:17:16,195 --> 00:17:17,260
And if your interest really is

414
00:17:17,295 --> 00:17:18,729
in getting him out of the courtroom,

415
00:17:18,764 --> 00:17:19,963
he was gonna do it himself.

416
00:17:19,998 --> 00:17:21,531
And why should I believe you?

417
00:17:21,566 --> 00:17:23,533
I can get you his letter of resignation.

418
00:17:23,568 --> 00:17:24,935
All you have to do is waive charges,

419
00:17:24,970 --> 00:17:28,638
and I'll get him to agree
never to practice law again.

420
00:17:29,421 --> 00:17:31,489
I'll tell you what I'll do.

421
00:17:31,524 --> 00:17:34,525
You get me that letter,
and I'll waive his bail.

422
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:35,726
I don't need you to waive bail.

423
00:17:35,761 --> 00:17:37,060
Whatever it is, he can pay for it.

424
00:17:37,096 --> 00:17:39,296
No, he can't. I'll freeze his assets.

425
00:17:39,331 --> 00:17:42,833
In fact, I'll make sure that
he doesn't get bail at all,

426
00:17:42,869 --> 00:17:45,035
because hacking into the
bar is a federal crime,

427
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:46,336
and if he can do that,

428
00:17:46,372 --> 00:17:48,271
he sure as hell can flee the country.

429
00:17:48,307 --> 00:17:50,509
You have no proof he
hacked into the bar.

430
00:17:50,510 --> 00:17:52,544
Doesn't matter. It's
what he's accused of.

431
00:17:52,579 --> 00:17:55,646
So you want to make sure he
walks out of court today,

432
00:17:55,682 --> 00:17:57,482
you bring me the letter.

433
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:11,507
That better be you calling
down to my office

434
00:18:11,543 --> 00:18:13,043
to explain why your golden boy

435
00:18:13,078 --> 00:18:15,145
was arrested for fraud last night.

436
00:18:15,180 --> 00:18:17,080
My golden boy?

437
00:18:17,115 --> 00:18:18,848
You're the one that
nominated him for partner.

438
00:18:18,883 --> 00:18:21,151
Because you passed him
over again and again,

439
00:18:21,186 --> 00:18:22,986
and I knew there was a reason for it,

440
00:18:23,021 --> 00:18:25,388
but now I know what it was.

441
00:18:25,424 --> 00:18:27,857
- Just what are you implying?
- I'm not implying anything.

442
00:18:27,892 --> 00:18:29,292
You knew that kid was a fraud,

443
00:18:29,328 --> 00:18:31,061
and even if you didn't, you should have.

444
00:18:31,096 --> 00:18:32,495
So what is it?

445
00:18:32,530 --> 00:18:34,264
Are you corrupt, or are
you just so stupid

446
00:18:34,299 --> 00:18:35,999
you didn't know what was
going on in your own firm?

447
00:18:36,034 --> 00:18:38,468
Watch who you're calling stupid, Jack,

448
00:18:38,503 --> 00:18:42,047
'cause you were the only idiot with his
hands in his pockets at that vote.

449
00:18:42,247 --> 00:18:43,271
I didn't have their support then,

450
00:18:43,307 --> 00:18:45,039
but I will now, because Harvey's protégé

451
00:18:45,075 --> 00:18:47,141
just got perp-walked out of this firm.

452
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:50,401
And since then, Harvey's
nowhere to be found.

453
00:18:50,436 --> 00:18:52,136
Harvey's whereabouts are
none of your concern.

454
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:53,738
Well, the partners are concerned.

455
00:18:53,773 --> 00:18:55,699
They need a leader they can trust.

456
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,700
And I'll bet someone's
trying to convince them

457
00:18:57,736 --> 00:18:58,735
that leader is you.

458
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:00,036
Well, look at that.

459
00:19:00,071 --> 00:19:02,439
You do know what's going on
in your own firm after all.

460
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:05,475
I'm gonna give you some advice
from the throne, free of charge.

461
00:19:05,511 --> 00:19:09,346
You attack this firm's
leadership when it's in crisis

462
00:19:09,381 --> 00:19:12,582
over an unproven allegation...

463
00:19:12,618 --> 00:19:15,084
you're gonna look like a bottom-feeder.

464
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:17,283
And even if they vote me out,

465
00:19:17,318 --> 00:19:20,387
they sure as hell won't vote you in.

466
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:28,206
Donna, what are you doing here?

467
00:19:28,241 --> 00:19:29,708
Gretchen told me you
weren't feeling well,

468
00:19:29,743 --> 00:19:31,142
so I dropped by to see how you're doing

469
00:19:31,177 --> 00:19:32,778
and tell you to cut the bullshit.

470
00:19:32,813 --> 00:19:34,145
I don't understand.

471
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:36,415
You've never taken a
sick day in your life,

472
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:37,549
and Mike just got arrested,

473
00:19:37,584 --> 00:19:39,684
so I want to know what
the hell is going on.

474
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,520
I can't be in the office right now.

475
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:44,556
Why not?

476
00:19:44,591 --> 00:19:46,190
Because I resigned.

477
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:47,992
What?

478
00:19:48,028 --> 00:19:49,294
Because of Mike?

479
00:19:49,329 --> 00:19:51,229
Because it's the only way to
get Forstman to back off.

480
00:19:51,264 --> 00:19:52,764
I don't care about Forstman.

481
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:55,166
You're leaving the firm
when we need you the most?

482
00:19:55,201 --> 00:19:58,837
Donna, right now I have to
stay away from the office,

483
00:19:58,872 --> 00:20:00,371
but I'm not leaving anyone.

484
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:01,506
I'm representing Mike.

485
00:20:01,542 --> 00:20:02,607
So you saw him.

486
00:20:02,643 --> 00:20:04,776
- Last night.
- And?

487
00:20:04,812 --> 00:20:05,877
He's hanging in.

488
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:08,648
I just need this bail
hearing to go smoothly.

489
00:20:08,649 --> 00:20:10,382
What do you mean, go smoothly?
What's going on?

490
00:20:10,418 --> 00:20:11,783
The prosecutor's playing hardball.

491
00:20:11,819 --> 00:20:13,285
She's trying to keep him without bail.

492
00:20:13,321 --> 00:20:15,154
Harvey, Rachel is not doing well.

493
00:20:15,189 --> 00:20:17,222
You have to get him out of there.

494
00:20:19,126 --> 00:20:20,192
Then I need you

495
00:20:20,227 --> 00:20:22,461
to get something from the office for me.

496
00:20:29,079 --> 00:20:29,996
"HI"

497
00:20:33,234 --> 00:20:35,835
I understand you've reached
an agreement to waive bail?

498
00:20:35,870 --> 00:20:36,836
We have, Your Honor.

499
00:20:36,871 --> 00:20:38,871
No bail is requested at this time.

500
00:20:38,906 --> 00:20:40,840
- Are you sure?
- Yes, I'm sure.

501
00:20:40,875 --> 00:20:42,842
However, I would like
to introduce a motion

502
00:20:42,877 --> 00:20:46,378
to have Mr. Specter removed
as attorney for Mr. Ross.

503
00:20:46,413 --> 00:20:47,612
- What?
- On what grounds?

504
00:20:47,648 --> 00:20:48,981
On the grounds that they conspired

505
00:20:49,016 --> 00:20:51,951
to defraud the bar association,
every client they ever had,

506
00:20:51,986 --> 00:20:53,452
and the people of the United States.

507
00:20:53,487 --> 00:20:54,954
What's your proof?

508
00:20:54,989 --> 00:20:57,456
This letter showing Mr.
Ross was going to resign.

509
00:20:57,491 --> 00:20:59,091
They conspired to fabricate it.

510
00:20:59,126 --> 00:21:01,293
- We had a deal.
- I don't care what we had.

511
00:21:02,146 --> 00:21:04,312
The two of them concocted a story

512
00:21:04,347 --> 00:21:06,414
under the guise of
attorney-client privilege,

