Yeah, it does, and you owe me, Trevor.

766
00:31:34,849 --> 00:31:36,116
I can't lie for you, Mike.

767
00:31:36,151 --> 00:31:37,417
I'm not asking you to lie for me.

768
00:31:37,453 --> 00:31:38,685
I'm asking you to pay me back

769
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:41,321
for every time in my life
you have screwed me over.

770
00:31:43,825 --> 00:31:45,358
Okay.

771
00:31:45,756 --> 00:31:47,522
But I'm not doing this
to make it up to you.

772
00:31:47,558 --> 00:31:49,223
I'm doing this to make sure my family

773
00:31:49,259 --> 00:31:50,725
doesn't get dragged into this.

774
00:31:50,761 --> 00:31:52,627
So don't bother me with this again,

775
00:31:52,663 --> 00:31:55,063
or I may just have to tell
them everything I know.

776
00:32:12,798 --> 00:32:13,897
I see you can dish it out.

777
00:32:13,933 --> 00:32:15,399
The question is, can you take a punch?

778
00:32:15,435 --> 00:32:16,667
Why don't you put the gloves on?

779
00:32:16,702 --> 00:32:17,835
We can find out.

780
00:32:17,870 --> 00:32:19,370
I don't know if you've noticed,

781
00:32:19,405 --> 00:32:21,339
but we're already in the ring,
and you're not in my class.

782
00:32:21,374 --> 00:32:22,440
What are you doing here?

783
00:32:22,475 --> 00:32:23,707
I just wanted to look you in the eye

784
00:32:23,743 --> 00:32:26,477
and ask if you still work
at Pearson Specter Litt.

785
00:32:26,513 --> 00:32:27,778
Excuse me?

786
00:32:27,813 --> 00:32:29,614
I stopped by your office
to see if you were serious

787
00:32:29,649 --> 00:32:31,649
about pleading this thing
out, and you weren't there.

788
00:32:31,684 --> 00:32:33,284
So I asked your secretary
when you'd be coming back,

789
00:32:33,319 --> 00:32:34,985
and she got very cagey.

790
00:32:35,021 --> 00:32:38,122
And now I find you here, boxing
in the middle of the day.

791
00:32:38,548 --> 00:32:39,947
I'm blowing off steam.

792
00:32:39,982 --> 00:32:41,314
I don't think so.

793
00:32:41,350 --> 00:32:44,852
I think I was wrong
about you and Mr. Ross

794
00:32:44,887 --> 00:32:46,954
fabricating a letter of resignation.

795
00:32:46,989 --> 00:32:48,589
And I think Jessica Pearson

796
00:32:48,624 --> 00:32:50,290
found out what you two were up to,

797
00:32:50,325 --> 00:32:52,225
and rather than making
herself look like a fool

798
00:32:52,261 --> 00:32:53,493
by handing you in,

799
00:32:53,529 --> 00:32:55,462
she forced you both to resign.

800
00:32:55,497 --> 00:32:57,064
And now you're on your own.

801
00:32:57,099 --> 00:32:58,432
And I think if you
want to write fiction,

802
00:32:58,467 --> 00:33:01,401
I hear they got a remedial class at NYU.

803
00:33:01,925 --> 00:33:03,891
Maybe I'm wrong.

804
00:33:03,927 --> 00:33:07,262
Maybe Jessica knew about
Mike Ross all along,

805
00:33:07,297 --> 00:33:11,232
in which case, maybe
you would turn on her.

806
00:33:11,268 --> 00:33:13,593
Why don't you get the hell out
of here before I turn on you?

807
00:33:13,836 --> 00:33:14,902
I will.

808
00:33:14,938 --> 00:33:16,904
But if I find out you resigned,

809
00:33:16,940 --> 00:33:18,773
that's evidence you're a co-conspirator.

810
00:33:18,808 --> 00:33:20,875
And I'll not only get you off this case.

811
00:33:20,910 --> 00:33:24,512
I'll put you behind bars
along with your little pet.

812
00:33:39,028 --> 00:33:40,027
What the hell is this?

813
00:33:40,062 --> 00:33:41,729
You know what it is. It's formal notice.

814
00:33:41,765 --> 00:33:43,364
Your services are no longer required.

815
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:44,799
I don't believe this.

816
00:33:44,834 --> 00:33:46,534
You're firing me? Yes, I am.

817
00:33:46,569 --> 00:33:47,902
And I want you to pack
your things up tonight,

818
00:33:47,937 --> 00:33:50,171
because you and I don't see eye
to eye on your priorities.

819
00:33:50,206 --> 00:33:51,872
Okay, Louis...

820
00:33:51,908 --> 00:33:53,174
just because we had a fight...

821
00:33:53,209 --> 00:33:55,335
No, this has nothing to do with that.

822
00:33:55,336 --> 00:33:56,803
So you're saying that
this has nothing to do

823
00:33:56,838 --> 00:33:57,937
with you lashing out at me

824
00:33:57,973 --> 00:33:59,338
because of the fight we had before?

825
00:33:59,374 --> 00:34:01,474
No, it doesn't, because
among other things,

826
00:34:01,509 --> 00:34:03,509
you set your own hours,
you can't take dictation,

827
00:34:03,545 --> 00:34:06,680
and to top all that, you
can't read people for shit!

828
00:34:09,151 --> 00:34:10,984
What's going on?

829
00:34:15,656 --> 00:34:19,257
You almost went to jail for
helping them once before,

830
00:34:19,292 --> 00:34:21,426
and I couldn't take that.

831
00:34:22,829 --> 00:34:26,064
And the thought of
losing you once again...

832
00:34:26,424 --> 00:34:29,092
So you know that they need my help.

833
00:34:29,127 --> 00:34:30,393
Yeah.

834
00:34:30,428 --> 00:34:32,695
I do.

835
00:34:32,730 --> 00:34:35,098
Now you're free to go.

836
00:34:36,105 --> 00:34:38,272
What made you change your mind?

837
00:34:38,307 --> 00:34:40,908
Jessica accused me of not
being a team player.

838
00:34:40,943 --> 00:34:44,811
And she was wrong about me, and...

839
00:34:44,847 --> 00:34:46,947
I was wrong about you.

840
00:34:48,251 --> 00:34:50,751
Thank you, Louis.

841
00:34:52,355 --> 00:34:53,354
I have to go.

842
00:34:53,389 --> 00:34:56,656
No, Louis.

843
00:34:56,692 --> 00:34:58,259
You don't.

844
00:35:17,750 --> 00:35:18,815
What are you doing here?

845
00:35:18,851 --> 00:35:20,884
Our conversation got cut
short the other night.

846
00:35:20,919 --> 00:35:22,553
So Anita Gibbs sent you here to tell me

847
00:35:22,588 --> 00:35:25,188
that if I go to prison, I'm
not gonna come out the same.

848
00:35:25,224 --> 00:35:26,457
You're right. She did.

849
00:35:26,492 --> 00:35:28,659
She wanted me to come here and
scare the shit out of you,

850
00:35:28,694 --> 00:35:29,727
tell you about everything

851
00:35:29,762 --> 00:35:31,262
that's gonna be happening to you inside.

852
00:35:31,297 --> 00:35:32,863
And who says I'm ever gonna be inside?

853
00:35:32,898 --> 00:35:34,265
Maybe you won't.

854
00:35:34,300 --> 00:35:36,233
But if you do, I'm here to tell you

855
00:35:36,269 --> 00:35:38,034
everything that's gonna
happen on the outside.

856
00:35:38,070 --> 00:35:39,536
Why don't you get the hell out of here?

857
00:35:39,572 --> 00:35:41,838
Listen to me. Anita's going
to come to you with a deal,

858
00:35:41,874 --> 00:35:43,607
and it's not gonna be
through Harvey Specter.

859
00:35:43,643 --> 00:35:45,175
And if you're smart, you'll take it.

860
00:35:45,210 --> 00:35:46,610
I said get the hell out.

861
00:35:46,646 --> 00:35:49,251
All right, I'll go. Just
let me tell you something.

862
00:35:49,252 --> 00:35:51,852
They don't have conjugal
visits in federal prison.

863
00:35:51,888 --> 00:35:54,755
And even if they did,
I've seen your fiancée.

864
00:35:54,791 --> 00:35:57,292
She's smart. She's beautiful.

865
00:35:57,327 --> 00:35:58,927
She has a future.

866
00:35:58,962 --> 00:36:00,528
Girls like that don't wait around,

867
00:36:00,563 --> 00:36:02,630
no matter what they say.

868
00:36:15,966 --> 00:36:18,434
Hey.

869
00:36:18,469 --> 00:36:20,769
Hey.

870
00:36:20,805 --> 00:36:22,838
- There's...
- I wanted to talk...

871
00:36:22,873 --> 00:36:26,542
Sorry. You go first.

872
00:36:26,577 --> 00:36:29,678
My father was here.

873
00:36:29,714 --> 00:36:33,181
That woman went to him
and offered a deal.

874
00:36:33,217 --> 00:36:35,283
Let me guess...

875
00:36:35,319 --> 00:36:37,519
they want me to turn on Harvey.

876
00:36:37,555 --> 00:36:38,854
They'll drop all the charges,

877
00:36:38,889 --> 00:36:42,249
and you won't have to
spend a minute in prison.

878
00:36:42,250 --> 00:36:43,516
What did you tell him?

879
00:36:43,552 --> 00:36:46,619
I told him that I would
give you the message.

880
00:36:47,343 --> 00:36:51,612
That you'd give me the message?

881
00:36:51,647 --> 00:36:53,848
Rachel, you know there's no way in hell

882
00:36:53,883 --> 00:36:55,583
I am ever gonna turn on them, right?

883
00:36:55,618 --> 00:36:57,017
- You know that.
- Yes, I do.

884
00:36:57,052 --> 00:36:58,586
- Do you?
- What's that supposed to mean?

885
00:36:58,621 --> 00:36:59,720
It means that you should have told him

886
00:36:59,756 --> 00:37:01,054
that I'm loyal to everyone in my life,

887
00:37:01,090 --> 00:37:02,590
and I would rather go to
jail than betray them.

888
00:37:02,625 --> 00:37:03,924
I did tell him that.

889
00:37:03,959 --> 00:37:05,559
So then why didn't you tell
me that you told him that?

890
00:37:05,595 --> 00:37:07,094
Because that's not what you asked me.

891
00:37:07,129 --> 00:37:08,829
Tell me right now that the
idea never crossed your mind

892
00:37:08,865 --> 00:37:09,997
that I should take this deal.

893
00:37:10,032 --> 00:37:12,266
Of course it popped into
my head for a second...

894
00:37:12,301 --> 00:37:13,868
So you think that I
should just turn on them

895
00:37:13,903 --> 00:37:15,302
the second things look bad?

896
00:37:15,337 --> 00:37:16,771
That is not what I said.

897
00:37:16,806 --> 00:37:19,759
Is that what you're
thinking of doing to me?

898
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:21,394
How could you even ask me that?

899
00:37:21,429 --> 00:37:22,962
I never even thought for a second

900
00:37:22,997 --> 00:37:25,798
that you would even consider
an idea so disgusting

901
00:37:25,833 --> 00:37:26,799
as turning on Harvey.

902
00:37:26,834 --> 00:37:28,167
The only reason I thought about it

903
00:37:28,202 --> 00:37:30,336
is because I am scared to death

904
00:37:30,371 --> 00:37:31,537
of you going to prison.

905
00:37:31,572 --> 00:37:32,671
Scared of me going to prison

906
00:37:32,706 --> 00:37:34,473
or scared that you can't stick around?

907
00:37:34,508 --> 00:37:35,942
Are you...?

908
00:37:38,593 --> 00:37:39,826
Mike, don't.

909
00:37:39,861 --> 00:37:42,429
We need to talk.

910
00:37:44,931 --> 00:37:47,365
We got a problem.

911
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:49,400
Yeah, we do...

912
00:37:49,435 --> 00:37:51,035
'cause it wasn't Trevor.

913
00:37:51,071 --> 00:37:53,371
It wasn't Scottie either,
but that's not our problem.

914
00:37:53,406 --> 00:37:56,007
Gibbs came to see me earlier. She
knows I'm not in the office.

915
00:37:56,042 --> 00:37:57,242
What does that mean?

916
00:37:57,277 --> 00:37:59,110
It means she's gonna try
to use it as evidence

917
00:37:59,146 --> 00:38:00,711
of Harvey being a co-conspirator,

918
00:38:00,747 --> 00:38:03,748
and if she does that,
Harvey can't represent me.

919
00:38:09,404 --> 00:38:12,105
What's going on?

920
00:38:12,140 --> 00:38:14,174
They offered Mike a deal.

921
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:16,009
They want him to turn on you.

922
00:38:17,045 --> 00:38:18,545
Then you're in good company,

923
00:38:18,581 --> 00:38:20,380
'cause they offered me a
deal to turn on Jessica,

924
00:38:20,415 --> 00:38:21,915
but that's not our problem.

925
00:38:21,951 --> 00:38:23,884
Our problem is figuring
out how to get me back

926
00:38:23,919 --> 00:38:26,386
without Forstman finding out.

927
00:38:27,006 --> 00:38:30,108
Wait a second.

928
00:38:30,143 --> 00:38:32,777
It doesn't matter if
Forstman finds out or not

929
00:38:32,812 --> 00:38:35,346
if he doesn't have someone on
the inside working for him.

930
00:38:35,382 --> 00:38:36,347
What are you saying?

931
00:38:36,383 --> 00:38:37,582
I'm saying that if they want me

932
00:38:37,617 --> 00:38:38,816
to point the finger at someone,

933
00:38:38,851 --> 00:38:40,685
that means I'm holding a gun.

934
00:38:49,730 --> 00:38:52,297
It's still alive.

935
00:38:53,834 --> 00:38:55,534
Did you think I would let it die?

936
00:38:55,569 --> 00:38:58,102
No, but I thought you
might give it away.

937
00:38:58,138 --> 00:39:01,145
Well, I'm more sentimental
than you think.

938
00:39:01,146 --> 00:39:02,145
How'd you get in here?

939
00:39:02,180 --> 00:39:03,347
Jessica told me how

940
00:39:03,382 --> 00:39:05,181
when I told her what I
was coming here to do.

941
00:39:05,217 --> 00:39:06,283
And what is that?

942
00:39:06,318 --> 00:39:08,719
You need me...

943
00:39:08,754 --> 00:39:10,887
because as good as Gretchen is,
she can't be a part of this,

944
00:39:10,922 --> 00:39:12,989
and you know it.

945
00:39:13,024 --> 00:39:15,992
You're saying you're coming back to me?

946
00:39:16,027 --> 00:39:19,162
Yes.

947
00:39:19,197 --> 00:39:22,132
I am.

948
00:39:22,779 --> 00:39:24,512
Good.

949
00:39:25,525 --> 00:39:27,826
Good.

950
00:39:30,596 --> 00:39:33,998
Then we'll see you back
in the office tomorrow.

951
00:39:34,034 --> 00:39:36,567
- What do you mean?
- I mean I'm coming back.

952
00:39:36,602 --> 00:39:37,936
How did you swing that?

953
00:39:37,971 --> 00:39:41,603
Hasn't happened yet, but I got a
little secret weapon called Mike Ross.

954
00:39:42,108 --> 00:39:45,076
Well, then...

955
00:39:46,708 --> 00:39:49,175
See you tomorrow.

956
00:39:51,587 --> 00:39:54,053
Donna?

957
00:39:55,524 --> 00:39:57,090
How did Louis take it?

958
00:39:57,125 --> 00:39:59,826
Believe it or not, it was his idea.

959
00:40:10,475 --> 00:40:12,208
Surprised to see me?

960
00:40:12,243 --> 00:40:13,877
As a matter of fact, I am,

961
00:40:13,912 --> 00:40:16,646
but as long as you're here,
I have a question for you.

962
00:40:17,916 --> 00:40:19,849
You want to know if it's true.

963
00:40:19,885 --> 00:40:21,150
Oh, I know it's true.

964
00:40:21,185 --> 00:40:22,719
I want to know why you haven't tried

965
00:40:22,754 --> 00:40:24,086
to deal your way out of this.

966
00:40:24,122 --> 00:40:26,222
You mean why haven't I turned
on Harvey and Jessica?

967
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:27,657
That's exactly what I mean.

968
00:40:27,692 --> 00:40:29,225
It wouldn't have anything to do

969
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:30,894
with you wanting to use all of this

970
00:40:30,929 --> 00:40:32,695
just to get your name
on the door, would it?

971
00:40:32,731 --> 00:40:33,963
Oh, I'm getting my name on the door

972
00:40:33,999 --> 00:40:35,331
whether you cut a deal or not.

973
00:40:35,366 --> 00:40:37,400
Well, if you don't stop coming
after Harvey and Jessica,

974
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:38,768
the only door you're gonna be looking at

975
00:40:38,803 --> 00:40:39,836
is gonna have bars on it.

976
00:40:39,871 --> 00:40:41,237
What the hell are you talking about?

977
00:40:41,272 --> 00:40:42,405
Let me tell you

978
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:44,073
what I just got finished
telling Daniel Hardman.

979
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:45,808
They're coming at me left and right

980
00:40:45,844 --> 00:40:47,844
to admit that someone around here knew

981
00:40:47,879 --> 00:40:51,013
what was going on with
me the whole time.

982
00:40:51,014 --> 00:40:52,847
So, if you don't back off

983
00:40:52,882 --> 00:40:55,116
trying to take over this
firm once and for all,

984
00:40:55,151 --> 00:40:57,185
I'm gonna tell them
that someone was you.

985
00:40:57,220 --> 00:40:58,353
Bullshit.

986
00:40:58,388 --> 00:41:00,388
You didn't even know me
until a few months ago.

987
00:41:00,424 --> 00:41:02,190
Well, yeah, but then you
and I worked together

988
00:41:02,225 --> 00:41:03,991
so closely on that case.

989
00:41:04,027 --> 00:41:06,160
And then I confided in you.

990
00:41:06,196 --> 00:41:10,164
And then you made me partner

991
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:12,801
so that you would always have an ally.

992
00:41:12,836 --> 00:41:15,002
There's no way that holds up in court.

993
00:41:15,038 --> 00:41:16,371
Good luck telling that to the judge.

994
00:41:16,878 --> 00:41:18,144
And this prosecutor...

995
00:41:18,627 --> 00:41:21,427
She... she's a real beast.

996
00:41:21,463 --> 00:41:23,622
She's gonna come after you
with everything she has.

997
00:41:24,614 --> 00:41:27,015
I never did anything to you.

998
00:41:27,051 --> 00:41:29,117
And I'm not leaving my firm.

999
00:41:29,153 --> 00:41:32,320
I don't give a shit whether
you stay or you go.

1000
00:41:32,355 --> 00:41:34,622
But Harvey is coming back
here tomorrow morning,

1001
00:41:34,658 --> 00:41:37,292
and if you pick up that phone
and call Charles Forstman,

1002
00:41:37,327 --> 00:41:38,860
then I am gonna pick up the phone

1003
00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:41,897
and tell that prosecutor
all about me and you.

1004
00:41:51,341 --> 00:41:54,275
I always wondered what
it was like in here.

1005
00:41:54,311 --> 00:41:56,178
It's nicer than I thought.

1006
00:41:56,213 --> 00:41:57,645
Jessica, how'd you find me here?

1007
00:41:57,681 --> 00:41:59,647
You always go mudding when you're upset.

1008
00:41:59,683 --> 00:42:02,117
I always go to the gun
range and the ballet.

1009
00:42:02,152 --> 00:42:04,753
You go to the range when you're angry,

1010
00:42:04,788 --> 00:42:06,254
the ballet when you're depressed,

1011
00:42:06,289 --> 00:42:07,655
but mud...

1012
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:09,224
Heals the broken heart.

1013
00:42:09,259 --> 00:42:10,391
I know.

1014
00:42:10,427 --> 00:42:12,227
And I heard about what
you did with Donna.

1015
00:42:12,262 --> 00:42:15,897
And I'm here to say I'm sorry.

1016
00:42:15,933 --> 00:42:19,267
You weren't just out for yourself.

1017
00:42:19,302 --> 00:42:20,902
But I was out for myself, Jessica.

1018
00:42:20,938 --> 00:42:22,104
Donna showed me that.

1019
00:42:22,139 --> 00:42:23,739
Are you saying you were after my job?

1020
00:42:23,774 --> 00:42:24,806
Of course I wasn't.

1021
00:42:24,842 --> 00:42:26,141
But who the hell am I kidding, you know?

1022
00:42:26,176 --> 00:42:28,409
